caller_intent: Christy from Auto Owners is following up on a renewal review for the M5 Group, inquiring about updates on building renovations post-fire, fire extinguisher status, and a handrail compliance issue.
resolution_steps: Jeff confirms three of four tenants have moved back into the M5 Group building, with the fourth expected by month-end.
He notes fire extinguishers are in place but highlights a pending handrail issue in the rear stairway, which Stan (M5 employee) is hesitant to address due to city code concerns.
Jeff agrees to send photos of fire extinguishers and follow up on occupant and step compliance issues.
He commits to pushing the renewal forward after confirming the current status.
knowledge_required: Navigating municipal code challenges for older buildings
summary: Christy from Auto Owners discusses the M5 Group's insurance renewal with Jeff, updating on building renovations post-fire. Three tenants have returned, fire extinguishers are installed, but a handrail issue remains unresolved due to city code concerns. Jeff agrees to send photos and follow up on compliance matters before finalizing the renewal.
